cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI

The paper analyzes the open access levels of scientific publications across all fields of research, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, based on the content of the paper, it is most likely to belong to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the availability of scientific publications online. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves collecting and analyzing data from Google Scholar. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses the reliability of different forms of access, cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the open access movement, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it mentions ResearchGate as a source of open access documents.
